09/02/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The minor parliamentary party New Time confirmed on Tuesday (8 February) that cabinet shuffles would be conducted within weeks, suggesting that its representatives would enter the coalition cabinet under a deal reached with the ruling coalition.
In other news Tuesday, Interior Ministry's Chief Secretary Boyko Borisov returned from talks at OSCE headquarters in Vienna. He said he suggested the OSCE establish a regional centre to fight trafficking in Bulgaria, which could be co-financed by the UN and the European Commission. (Monitor - 09/02/05; bTV, Mediapool - 08/02/05)
